Quantum-resistant (or post-quantum) cryptography is the branch of cryptography designed to withstand attacks from quantum computers â€” which can break many of the classical algorithms (like RSA, ECC, and DH) that we currently rely on.

    In short: Quantum computers threaten asymmetric cryptography, and post-quantum cryptography (PQC) is our defense.

